                Backend for E-commerce
1   create package.json - npm init
2   create nodemodules - install express - npm i express
3   create index.js file

    -------on indexfile--------
4   import express inside the index.js
5   create application 
6   set up port number
7   use json parser for server application

8   install cors - npm i cors
9   import cors
10  using cors specify origin to the server

11  api fetch - fakestoreapi/products
12  create DB and collection in mongoDB
13 install mongoose to establish connection b/w server and mongoDB 
        npm i mongoose

14  create a folder - Services
        create file - db.js and dataService.js
15  In db.js - import mongoose to establish connection
16  define connection string
17  create model and schema 
18  export model (Product) 

19  Resolving API request in index.js
20  implement logic in dataService
21  import db in dataService,sreate a function and  export it
22  Resolving API request in index.js (to implement logic in dataService)
        index+dataService
        Node + mongoDB connection successfull

23  final step
    API to get all products





